{"product_name": "Provided by ManualsAndMore.com", "content": ["Meet your\nnew phone", "xfinitymobile", "SAMSUNG\nGalaxy S9|S9+", "A map of the hardware", "!image\nmicroSD/SIM Front\ncard tray camera\nIris\n100% scanner\n12\nVolume\n45 Power/\nLock\nFRI, MARCH 16\nBixby\nEdge Edge\nscreen screen\nHeadset\njack USB/\ncharger port", "!image\nRear Dual\ncamera camera\nSAMSUNG\nSAMSUNG\nGalaxy S9 Galaxy S9+", "Access the edge", "With edge screen technology, access people,\ninformation, and apps in a flash.", "To turn on the edge screen feature, start at the\nHome screen and swipe up for Apps. Then tap", "Settings > Display > Edge screen.", "!image\nall 100% ■ 12:45 PM\n43°\nSwipe to view\nedge screen.\nNew York City\nUpdated 03/16 12:45 Q Drag a\nnotification for\nmore details.\nOJ\nPhone Messages Internet Play Store Camera", "Apps edge", "Create shortcuts to access frequently\nused apps.", "People edge", "See missed calls and message notifications\nfrom your important contacts.", "Smart select", "Capture images and GIF animations.", "Say hello to Bixby!", "Hello Bixby lets you set reminders and create\nvoice dictations. Plus, quickly search for content\non your phone and across the Internet.", "To launch Hello Bixby, simply press the\nBixby button.", "!image\nBixby", "NOTE: For more information about Bixby, visit\nsamsung.com/us/support/owners/app/Baby", "Steps to phone setup", "Charge up", "To charge your phone, first connect the\nAdaptive Fast Charger to the USB cable, and\nconnect the USB to your phone. Then plug the\nAdaptive Fast Charger into an outlet. Keep your\nphone plugged in until it reaches 100% battery.", "!image", "WARNING: Use only Samsung-approved charging devices.\nSamsung accessories are designed to maximize battery life.\nUsing other accessories may invalidate your warranty and may\ncause damage.", "Activate!", "Before you turn on your phone, activate\nyour service. On another device, go to\nxfinitymobile.com/activate. Log in and\nyou'll be walked through the process.", "microSD/SIM card tray\nIf you have a microSD card, insert it here:", "!image\nWISD\nxfinity\nwroson", "NOTE: To access the microSD card slot, remove the\nmicroSD/SIM card tray from the device.", "The how-to basics", "Powering on and off", "To turn your phone on, press and hold the\nPower/Lock button. Once it's on, press and\nhold that same button to power it off.", "!image", "The screen basics", "To turn on your screen, press the Power/Lock\nbutton, then swipe up onscreen to unlock it.\nTo turn your screen off, just press the\nPower/Lock button.", "!image\n↑", "Using the Xfinity Mobile app", "The Xfinity Mobile app is preloaded on\nyour phone. Consider it your control center\nto track your usage, manage your account,\nand ask us anything.", "!image\nxfInIty\n○", "Voicemail 101", "Listen to your messages or read them\nas text. You can also record a custom\nvoicemail greeting.", "!image\nQO", "Need help? We're here.\nDial our support line: 1 (888) 936-4968", "Copyright 2018 Samsung Electronics Company, Ltd. Samsung,\nGalaxy S9, Galaxy S9+ and Samsung Pay, are trademarks of\nSamsung Electronics Co., Ltd. Google, Android, Google Play\nand other marks are trademarks of Google LLC. Screen images\nsimulated. Appearance of device may vary.\nThe Xfinity Mobile logo and the New Network mark (\"O\")\nare trademarks of Comcast. All rights reserved.", "Printed in Korea.", "GH68-48871A"], "flag": true}
